              Girl, Interrupted (1999) Film
{_________________________________________________________}
In 1967, after a session with a psychiatrist she'd never seen before, Susanna Kaysen was diagnosed 
with Borderline Personality Disorder-an affliction with symptoms so ambiguous almost any adolescent girl might qualify
and sent to a renowned New England psychiatric hospital where she spent the next two years in a ward for teenage girls. 
There, Susanna loses herself in an OZ-like nether world of seductive and disturbed young women among them Lisa,
a charming sociopath who stages a disastrous escape with Susanna, Daisy a pampered girl with a predilection for rotisserie chicken,
and Polly, a remarkably kind burn victim. Ultimately, assisted by the hospital's head psychiatrist,Dr. Wick,
and a no-nonsense ward nurse, Valerie, Susanna, like Dorothy, resolves to leave this Oz and reclaim her life.
